==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haematoin
<hw>Hae*mat"o*in</hw> <pr>(h⟦esl⟧*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦osl⟧*⟦icr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Haemato-</ets> + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A substance formed from the hematin of
blood, by removal of the iron through the action of concentrated
sulphuric acid. Two like bodies, called respectively
<xex>haematoporphyrin</xex> and <xex>haematolin</xex>, are formed in a
similar manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haematolin</ent>⟦br⟧
